name: Ella T Johnson
text: Pronouns: She/Her/Hers lauren.cooper@myfloridahouse.gov Florida State House District 47 Representative Anna V. Eskamani District Senior Executive Secretary Lauren Cooper Lauren Stay safe and speak soon! We also encourage you to keep in touch with us online where we share constant updates on current events and legislative advocacy with a recent emphasis on DEO coverage. You can find our team online on Twitter Facebook and Instagram at @AnnaForFlorida. Please know that the issues with DEO are not your own fault and we are working hard and often to keep Floridians informed and hold the state accountable. Note: If you have other claim issues please consider filling out our Claim Escalation Form here which we will manually migrate into the DEO Escalation Portal to request a caseworker review your benefits ASAP. Finally we understand that this system has harmed Floridians far and wide. We are committed to systemic change and Rep. Eskamani voted yes to return to Tallahassee and fix unemployment ASAP  however this measure failed by a party line vote in May. She also joined a cohort of lawmakers in requesting more tools for lawmakers to help claimants however DEO has not since responded. It incredibly disappointing to hear that DEO continues to make mistakes with claims and wel be asking DEO to expedite the list we have sent them. From DEO: ndividuals who requested that their claims be backdated were not included in recent payment files for the Federal Pandemic Unemployment Compensation payments. We are working diligently to ensure these claimants are made whole as quickly as possible. At this time claimants do not need to do anything but should continue to request benefits as long as they are unemployed or partially unemployed. The department anticipates having the issue resolved quickly and being able to provide these payments to eligible claimants. Additionally the department has identified that some claimants were not paid their Federal Pandemic Unemployment Compensation payment for their waiting week. The department has identified these individuals and should have them paid their $600 federal payment within five business days. Earlier this evening DEO shared that there are wo technology concerns that may have prevented an individual from receiving their Federal Pandemic Unemployment Compensation payment over the last few weeks. This message is a confirmation that our team received your submission to our Missing FPUC Payments Form to request assistance with $600 payments since May 19th. We have closed the form at 9:00pm and Representative Eskamani has since shared your submitted details to the Legislative Affairs Team at DEO which liaises between lawmakers and claim caseworkers. Lauren here with Representative Anna Eskamani. Anna Allshouse I received this email yesterday after asking questions for weeks. Good Evening

text: DEO says PUA claims for independent contractors will be automatically be paid retroactive. This is not true. My wife is a Nail Technician with a 1099-MISC from 2019 and became unemployed on 3/19/2020 due to COVID 19. She started her application on 3/29/2020 after CARES was signed. It finally went through on 4/4/2020 but was denied because she was an independent contractor. She filed on the new website as advised and that has been in \Pending - Submitted\ since 4/14/2020. She filed for PUA on 5/22/2020 and the PUA application shows she became unemployed on 3/19/2020. Even DEO guide says these are automatically made retroactive but she received two weeks of PUA starting 5/10/2020 and nothing retroactive. DEO does not answer emails and it's impossible to get through on the phone. She is back to work so PUA has stopped but she never received the retroactive payments. Her PUA application on CONNECT shows a start date of 5/10/2020. I keep seeing that these are automatically aid to the date they lost work NOT the application date but this just isn't true. How do we get this fixed when DEO never answers emails or pick up the phone?

name: Lulu App
text: Also if you pay for health insurance at work make sure the amount of unemployment they're giving you is based on how much you MADE not how much you took home after paying for your health insurance. My mom pays for health insurance provided from her job and for some reason her unemployment amount was based on what she made after paying her health insurance which is incorrect. My sister also works for the mouse (disney) and pays insurance and she got the correct unemployment amount based on how much money she made without deducting the amount that went for health insurance so keep an eye our for that. We're still waiting to hear from them to fix this issue so she can get the money she is owed. -PSA. You wont see the link for PEUC until you request the funds for your last week. My last week was June 7-13 but my request date was June 22nd. I went in June 22nd and requested the funds for June 7-13 and it let me request funds for June 14-20 as well. No link for PEUC had shown up yet. The following date I go in and the link finally showed up. It asked me 19 yes or no questions and once I submitted it I went back to my home page and boom I was already enrolled in PEUC. My balanced (benefit amount) went up for 13 weeks my claim status is now \exhausted_active\ and the program type is now \Pandemic EUC.\ Instead of getting paid for my two weeks at once how I normally did my funds for the week of June 7-13 showed up on my bank account on June 24 and the funds for the week of June 14-20 is currently pending to be deposited on my bank account. My fund request date has also been moved up a week so instead of going in in July to request my two weeks I go back in on the 29th.
